Mix cookie crumbs, coconut and 1/2 cup melted butter. Press firmly onto bottom of 9-inch square pan. Refrigerate until ready to use. Beat pudding mix, 1/3 cup softened butter and hot water. Add powdered sugar; beat until well blended. Spread over crust. Refrigerate 2 hours or until filling is set. Microwave chocolate and 1 tablespoon butter on high power (100%) for 1 minute. Stir until chocolate is completely melted. Spread over pudding layer; refrigerate until set. Cut into bars to serve. Store leftover dessert in refrigerator.